# URL of the docTracking API server.
# Leave unset when the client is served by the same Express server as the
# API (the normal single-port deployment) — requests default to the
# same origin the page was loaded from, so no server address is baked
# into the public JS bundle.
# Only set this for a split deployment where the client and API are on
# different origins. Use a public hostname, never an internal/private IP —
# this value is compiled as a literal string into the client bundle that
# ships to every browser, unauthenticated.
#REACT_APP_API_URL=https://api.example.com
